#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an4.246"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.246:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.246:0.2"
msgid "25. Āpattibhayavagga "
msgstr "25. Perils of Offenses "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.246:0.3"
msgid "246. Seyyāsutta "
msgstr "246. Lying Postures "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an4.246:1.1"
msgid "“Catasso imā, bhikkhave, seyyā. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these four ways of lying down. "

msgctxt "an4.246:1.2"
msgid "Katamā catasso? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "an4.246:1.3"
msgid "Petaseyyā, kāmabhogiseyyā, sīhaseyyā, tathāgataseyyā. "
msgstr "The ways a corpse, a pleasure seeker, a lion, and a Realized One lie down. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.246:1.4"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, petaseyyā? "
msgstr "And how does a corpse lie down? "

msgctxt "an4.246:1.5"
msgid "Yebhuyyena, bhikkhave, petā uttānā senti; "
msgstr "Corpses usually lie flat on their backs. "

# NOTE: Still called the “corpse posture” in yoga!
msgctxt "an4.246:1.6"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, petaseyyā. "
msgstr "This is called the way a corpse lies down. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an4.246:2.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, kāmabhogiseyyā? "
msgstr "And how does a pleasure seeker lie down? "

msgctxt "an4.246:2.2"
msgid "Yebhuyyena, bhikkhave, kāmabhogī vāmena passena senti; "
msgstr "Pleasure seekers usually lie down on their left side. "

msgctxt "an4.246:2.3"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, kāmabhogiseyyā. "
msgstr "This is called the way a pleasure seeker lies down. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.245, sc3
msgctxt "an4.246:3.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, sīhaseyyā? "
msgstr "And how does a lion lie down? "

msgctxt "an4.246:3.2"
msgid "Sīho, bhikkhave, migarājā dakkhiṇena passena seyyaṃ kappeti, pāde pādaṃ accādhāya, antarasatthimhi naṅguṭṭhaṃ anupakkhipitvā. "
msgstr "The lion, king of beasts, lies down on the right side, placing one foot on top of the other, with his tail tucked between his thighs. "

msgctxt "an4.246:3.3"
msgid "So paṭibujjhitvā purimaṃ kāyaṃ abbhunnāmetvā pacchimaṃ kāyaṃ anuviloketi. "
msgstr "When he wakes, he lifts his front quarters and checks his hind quarters. "

msgctxt "an4.246:3.4"
msgid "Sace, bhikkhave, sīho migarājā kiñci passati kāyassa vikkhittaṃ vā visaṭaṃ vā, tena, bhikkhave, sīho migarājā anattamano hoti. "
msgstr "If he sees that any part of his body is disordered or displaced, he is displeased. "

msgctxt "an4.246:3.5"
msgid "Sace pana, bhikkhave, sīho migarājā na kiñci passati kāyassa vikkhittaṃ vā visaṭaṃ vā, tena, bhikkhave, sīho migarājā attamano hoti. "
msgstr "But if he sees that no part of his body is disordered or displaced, he is pleased. "

msgctxt "an4.246:3.6"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, sīhaseyyā. "
msgstr "This is called the way a lion lies down. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an4.246:4.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, tathāgataseyyā? "
msgstr "And how does a Realized One lie down? "

msgctxt "an4.246:4.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, tathāgato vivicceva kāmehi … pe … catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "It’s when a Realized One, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption … second absorption … third absorption … fourth absorption. "

msgctxt "an4.246:4.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, tathāgataseyyā. "
msgstr "This is called the way a Realized One lies down. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.246:4.4"
msgid "Imā kho, bhikkhave, catasso seyyā”ti. "
msgstr "These are the four ways of lying down.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.246:4.5"
msgid "Catutthaṃ. "
msgstr ""

